            <glossentry id="wsrf">
                  <glossterm>Web Services Resource Framework</glossterm>
                  <acronym>WSRF</acronym>
                  <glossdef>
                        <para>Web Services Resource Framework (WSRF) is a specification that extends web services for grid applications by giving them the ability
                              to retain state information while at the same time retaining statelessness (using resources). The combination of a web service and a resource
                              is referred to as a WS-Resource.
                              The Web Services Resources Framework is a collection of different specifications that manage WS-Resources.</para>

                        <para>For more information, go to: <ulink url="http://www.globus.org/wsrf/">http://www.globus.org/wsrf/</ulink>.</para>
                  </glossdef>
            </glossentry>
